## SS 5. Schedule Tasks

**Read BROWSER-engage.md first** (for like/search/subscribe tasks).

Filter: `status="pending" AND time<=now`, sort by time.
**No spacing rule.** Execute tasks back-to-back when due.

### Content-Ready Override (publish tasks only)

Before executing any `publish_newsletter` or `publish_note` task:

1. Read the file at `config.content_source`
2. For notes: Find the first post with `status: pending`, use that content
3. For newsletters: Use the full newsletter content
4. After verified publish → update the file: change `status: pending` to `status: published` for that post

**Task types:**

- **browse_and_engage** -> Optimized workflow:
  🚨 **Prefer Notes over article comments.** Notes engagement on `substack.com` is reliable. Article comments on custom domains (`*.org`, `*.com`, `*.io`) are often inaccessible (iframe/embed issues). If article comments fail once → switch to Notes feed immediately, do NOT retry.
  1. **Search/browse** — Start with Substack Notes feed (`substack.com` home) or search. MAX 2 search queries per heartbeat.
  2. **Extract posts** — BROWSER-engage.md SS 5. Filter: recent posts (< 14 days), has engagement.
  3. **🚨 MANDATORY batch grep pre-check BEFORE navigating** — check ALL candidate URLs at once:
     ```bash
     exec printf '%s\n' "slug1" "slug2" "slug3" | while read line; do grep -qF "$line" memory/commented_posts.txt && echo "SKIP: $line" || echo "OK: $line"; done
     ```
     Only navigate to "OK:" posts.
  4. Per selected post (grep returned "OK"): Navigate to `{post_url}/comments` directly. Then **paywall probe + dedup check (ONE evaluate):**
     ```javascript
     async () => {
       await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 5000));
       var textarea = document.querySelector('textarea[name="body"]');
       if (!textarea) return { canComment: false, paywall: true };
       // Probe: type a char to trigger paid-only popup (Substack shows textarea but blocks on submit)
       textarea.focus();
       textarea.value = 'x';
       textarea.dispatchEvent(new Event('input', { bubbles: true }));
       await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1500));
       var paidPopup = document.body.innerText.includes('Only paid subscribers can comment');
       if (paidPopup) return { canComment: false, paywall: true, reason: 'paid_subscribers_only' };
       // Clear probe text
       textarea.value = '';
       textarea.dispatchEvent(new Event('input', { bubbles: true }));
       // Dedup check (post pages only - skip on /note/ URLs)
       var url = window.location.href;
       var hasOwnComment = false;
       if (!url.includes('/note/')) {
         hasOwnComment = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('a')).some(a => (a.href || '').includes('/@{{handle}}'));
       }
       return { canComment: true, paywall: false, alreadyCommented: hasOwnComment };
     }
     ```
     If `paywall: true` → skip immediately. If `alreadyCommented: true` → backfill tracking, skip.
     Otherwise: Like post (BROWSER-engage.md SS 4, scroll up) -> 🚨 **Apply Comment Quality Rules** (BROWSER-engage.md §A/B/C/D/E/F) -> comment (BROWSER-core.md SS 3, textarea already visible) -> **after commenting: subscribe** if not already subscribed and `daily.subscribes.current < limit` (BROWSER-engage.md SS 6) -> restack with a note if high-quality and `daily.restacks.current < limit` (BROWSER-restack.md SS 10)
  4b. **🚨 Restack at least 1 post per browse_and_engage task** if restack limit not reached. Pick the best post from the batch. A restack with a quote note puts your take into the original author's audience feed — free visibility.
  4c. **🚨 Subscribe is tied to commenting.** Every time you comment on a post, subscribe to that author's publication (if not already subscribed and limit not reached). The author sees both notifications — comment + subscribe — which signals genuine engagement.
  5. 🚨 **ONLY append to `commented_posts.txt` AFTER a verified posted comment.**
     ```bash
     exec printf '%s\n' '{post_url}' >> memory/commented_posts.txt
     ```
  6. Log: Type=Like, Type=Comment, Type=Subscribe, Type=Restack
  7. Completion: increment `comments_done`, `likes_done`, `restacks_done`. If limits reached -> mark "done". Else "pending".

- **notes_engagement** -> Browse Substack Notes feed, like and reply to relevant notes. Short, punchy replies. Log Type=Note.

- **publish_note** -> Write and publish a short-form note to the Substack feed. Workflow:
  1. Read queries.json topics, INSIGHTS.md for what resonates
  2. Draft note (100-500 chars, punchy, conversational - NOT article-length). Add 3-5 hashtags at end (read from `queries.json → hashtags` array — refreshed daily).
  3. Self-review (TOOLS.md SS Self-Review Gate)
  4. Click "New post" button in nav (opens Notes composer, NOT article editor)
  5. Type into `div[contenteditable="true"]` (paste approach)
  6. Verify "Anyone can reply" is set (button visible in composer)
  7. Click "Post" button (enabled after content typed)
  8. Verify: composer closes, note visible in feed
  9. Log Type=Note, content snippet, URL
  10. Update `limits.json -> daily.notes_posted.current++`
  🚨 **"New post" button opens Notes composer.** Dashboard "Create post" opens article editor. Different flows.
  🚨 **Notes composer uses contenteditable** (same as note replies). Paste approach.
  🚨 **Post button is disabled until content is typed.** Dispatch InputEvent after paste.

- **publish_newsletter** -> Write and publish a newsletter post. Workflow:
  1. Read queries.json topics, INSIGHTS.md for what resonates
  2. Pick topic from content pillars (SOUL.md), draft article (1000-2000 words)
  3. **Format body as HTML** — use `<h2>` for headings, `<strong>` for bold, `<em>` for italic, `<a href="https://substack.com/@handle">Name</a>` for writer references, `<ul><li>` for lists, `<blockquote>` for quotes. See BROWSER-publish.md Step 3 for full list.
  4. Self-review (TOOLS.md SS Self-Review Gate)
  5. Navigate to `{{handle}}.substack.com/publish/post` (creates new draft)
  6. Fill: `textarea[placeholder="Title"]`, `textarea[placeholder*="subtitle"]`, body via `div[contenteditable="true"]` (HTML paste approach)
  7. Wait for auto-save ("Saved" button)
  8. Click "Continue" -> set Audience: Everyone, Comments: Everyone (second radio group `value="everyone"`)
  9. Click "Send to everyone now"
  10. Verify: page navigates to share-center with "Your post is live!"
  11. Log Type=Article, title, URL
  12. Update `limits.json -> weekly.newsletters.current++`
  🚨 **Both Audience AND Comments default to "only_paid"** — MUST set BOTH radio groups to `value="everyone"`.
  🚨 **Editor uses HTML paste:** `dt.setData('text/html', html)` for rich formatting. See BROWSER-publish.md Step 3.
  🚨 **Title/subtitle use textarea:** Set `.value` + dispatch `input` + `change` events.
  🚨 **Navigate to `{{handle}}.substack.com/publish/post`** (no ID) to create a new draft. Do NOT use "New post" nav button (opens Notes composer).

- **restack** -> Restack (retweet) relevant notes/posts with a quote note. Workflow:
  1. During browse_and_engage or notes_engagement, identify high-quality content worth restacking
  2. Click "Restack" button on the note/post -> menu appears with "Restack" (simple) and "Restack with a note" (quote)
  3. Prefer "Restack with a note" (menuitem) - adds our perspective, builds brand
  4. Notes composer opens with original embedded -> type quote text + 3-5 hashtags from `queries.json → hashtags` into `div[contenteditable="true"]` (paste approach)
  5. Click "Post" button
  6. Verify: composer closes
  7. Log Type=Restack, original author, our note snippet
  8. Update `limits.json -> daily.restacks.current++`
  🚨 **Restack button opens a dropdown menu** with two menuitems: "Restack" and "Restack with a note". Use snapshot to find refs.
  🚨 **Quote composer is identical to Notes composer** - same contenteditable + Post button.
  🚨 **Prefer "Restack with a note"** over plain restack - adds value and visibility.

- **recommend** -> Recommend a relevant publication. Workflow:
  1. Read BROWSER-recommend.md
  2. Read `memory/recommended_publications.txt` for already-recommended publications
  3. Choose candidate: check recent `memory/{date}.md` for writers we've engaged with, cross-reference `queries.json` topics. Prefer writers with reciprocal comment exchanges, active posting, and audience-relevant content.
  4. Dedup check: `grep -qF "{publication_name}" memory/recommended_publications.txt`
  5. Navigate to recommendations dashboard (BROWSER-recommend.md SS 2 Step 0)
  6. Add recommendation with search + reason (BROWSER-recommend.md SS 2 Steps 1-3)
  7. After verified success: append to tracking file
  8. Log: Type=Recommend, Publication, Reason (100 chars)
  9. Update limits: `recommendations.current++`
  🚨 **Reason must be specific and relevant** — explain why your PM/AI audience will benefit. Not generic praise.
  🚨 **Read BROWSER-recommend.md ON-DEMAND** only when a `recommend` task is due.

- **update_memory** -> PLAYBOOK.md SS Memory Update

**MANDATORY: Task stays "pending" until ALL configured limits reached.**

